
Paris, 8 March 1780.. RC in John Thaxters hand (PCC, No. 84, I, f. 311). LbC (Adams Papers); notation in Thaxters hand: March 10th. Delivered [25]the above to Mr Brown of Charlestown S. Carolina.printed: Wharton, ed., Dipl. Corr. Amer. Rev., 3:539.
In this letter, read by Congress on 11 Sept., John Adams reported the false rumor that Louis Charles, Comte du Chaffault de Besn was to command in the West Indies and Charles Henri Thodat, Comte dEstaing in the Channel, and enclosed newspapers from Paris, The Hague, and Amsterdam, all dating from the first week in March.
